Preheat your oven to 200°C and put your #kettle{} on to boil. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} and pepper, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook until the chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally. Meanwhile, put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Pour in the @water for the sauce{75%ml} and add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @tomato passata{1} into the pan with the chicken. Stir in the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium until the sauce is simmering away. Cook until the sauce has thickened and the veggies are soft, stirring occasionally, about ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan. Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and season with salt and pepper.

Add half the parsley to the chicken and veggies and stir through. Transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the creamy pasta. Cover with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and pop on the top shelf of your #oven{}. Bake until the top is golden and a little crunchy at the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Serve the chicken pasta bake in #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Enjoy!